Di Zhang,1 Tarja-Leena Penttila ,3 Patricia L. Morris,2,3 |XML| xmlLoc_1 xmlBold_no xmlItalic_no xmlFontSize_none xmlPic_yes xmlTable_no xmlBullet_no bi_xmlSFBIA_continue bi_xmlPara_new
Martin Teichmann,1 Robert G. Roeder1* |XML| xmlLoc_1 xmlBold_no xmlItalic_no xmlFontSize_none xmlPic_yes xmlTable_no xmlBullet_no bi_xmlSFBIA_continue bi_xmlPara_continue
The discovery of TATA-binding protein–related factors (TRFs) has suggested |XML| xmlLoc_2 xmlBold_no xmlItalic_no xmlFontSize_none xmlPic_yes xmlTable_no xmlBullet_no bi_xmlSFBIA_new bi_xmlPara_new
alternative mechanisms for gene-specific transcriptional regulation and raised |XML| xmlLoc_2 xmlBold_no xmlItalic_no xmlFontSize_none xmlPic_yes xmlTable_no xmlBullet_no bi_xmlSFBIA_continue bi_xmlPara_continue
interest in their biological functions. In contrast to recent observations of an |XML| xmlLoc_2 xmlBold_no xmlItalic_no xmlFontSize_none xmlPic_yes xmlTable_no xmlBullet_no bi_xmlSFBIA_continue bi_xmlPara_continue
embryonic lethal phenotype for TRF2 inactivation in Caenorhabditis elegans and |XML| xmlLoc_2 xmlBold_no xmlItalic_no xmlFontSize_none xmlPic_yes xmlTable_no xmlBullet_no bi_xmlSFBIA_continue bi_xmlPara_continue
Xenopus laevis, we found that Trf2-deficient mice are viable. However, Trf2–/– |XML| xmlLoc_2 xmlBold_no xmlItalic_no xmlFontSize_none xmlPic_yes xmlTable_no xmlBullet_no bi_xmlSFBIA_continue bi_xmlPara_continue
mice are sterile because of a severe defect in spermiogenesis. Postmeiotic round |XML| xmlLoc_2 xmlBold_no xmlItalic_no xmlFontSize_none xmlPic_yes xmlTable_no xmlBullet_no bi_xmlSFBIA_continue bi_xmlPara_continue
spermatids advance at most to step 7 of differentiation but fail to progress to |XML| xmlLoc_2 xmlBold_no xmlItalic_no xmlFontSize_none xmlPic_yes xmlTable_no xmlBullet_no bi_xmlSFBIA_continue bi_xmlPara_continue
the elongated form, and gene-specific transcription deficiencies were identified. |XML| xmlLoc_3 xmlBold_no xmlItalic_no xmlFontSize_none xmlPic_yes xmlTable_no xmlBullet_no bi_xmlSFBIA_continue bi_xmlPara_continue
We speculate that mammals may have evolved more specialized TRF2 functions |XML| xmlLoc_3 xmlBold_no xmlItalic_no xmlFontSize_none xmlPic_yes xmlTable_no xmlBullet_no bi_xmlSFBIA_continue bi_xmlPara_continue
in the testis that involve transcriptional regulation of genes essential for |XML| xmlLoc_3 xmlBold_no xmlItalic_no xmlFontSize_none xmlPic_yes xmlTable_no xmlBullet_no bi_xmlSFBIA_continue bi_xmlPara_continue
spermiogenesis. |XML| xmlLoc_3 xmlBold_no xmlItalic_no xmlFontSize_none xmlPic_yes xmlTable_no xmlBullet_no bi_xmlSFBIA_continue bi_xmlPara_continue
